GateDocument.TextWithNodes: Sponsored by COST 211 quat FIRST ANNOUNCEMENT Call for Papers W I A M I S ' 9 9 Workshop on Image Analysis for Multimedia Interactive Services 31 May and 1 June 1999 Heinrich- Hertz- Institute ( HHI ) Berlin , Germany The 2 nd European Workshop on Image Analysis for Multimedia Interactive Services will be held on 31 May and 1 June 1999 at Heinrich- Hertz- Institute Berlin , Germany . The objective of the workshop is to provide a forum for discussion of new and recent results on techniques for advanced image analysis and image processing for emerging interactive multimedia services in the context of MPEG- 4 and MPEG- 7 . Active participation from researchers within and from outside of Europe is encouraged in order to preserve its characteristic as a workshop . Authors are invited to submit an abstract of approx . 1000 words . Final contributions in form of a four page paper and a 20 minutes oral presentation are being sought for accepted contributions . Areas of interest are targeted for both real-time and non real-time audio-visual applications and include , but are not limited to : - Supervised and unsupervised segmentation - Indexing of images , video , audio , speech of objects in 2 - D / 3 - D image sequencesMotion / texture / shape descriptors - Identification and tracking of regions in scenes - 2 - D / 3 - D feature extraction - Voice / audio assisted image / video segmentation - Feature-based image / video query - Searching and browsing of audiovisual data - Content generation and manipulation In submitting papers please take into account the following deadlines 10 March 1999 Submission of Abstracts ( 3 copies ) 15 April 1999 Notification of acceptance mailed 10 May 1999 Submission of camera ready paper ( 4 pages ) Please direct enquiries or submissions of abstracts and papers to : WIAMIS'99 Secretariat Regina Kiesewetter Heinrich- Hertz- Institute Berlin for Communication Technology Human Factors Department Einsteinufer 37 , 10587 Berlin , Germany Tel : + 49 - 30 - 31002 211 Fax . : + 49 - 30 - 31002 213 Email : kiesewetter @ sjyk . jbb . kna Chairperson : - - - - - - - - - - - - T .
